1. Use make to compile

2. The port number is defined in the program.

3. Execute commands: ./server
                    ./client pyrite <command> or ./client pyrite-n2 <command>

4. Output redirect fixed.

5. Attempted to implement multiple commands, i.e. <_;_;_>, but not working.

6. Parent process on the server uses wait() to reap zombie processes.

7. Commands with spaces and flags do not work.

8. Server can run single commands multiple times.

9. "History" and "Jobs" commands not implemented.

10. Encryption and decryption should work fine.

